<h1>Error Handling</h1>

Errors are shown in two formats: <b>HTTP-Status Codes</b> and <b>Exceptions</b>.

<h2 id="http-status-codes">HTTP-Status Codes</h2>

<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes" target="_blank">HTTP-Status Codes</a>
are used to express errors covered by the HTTP protocol. Errors associated with the communication 
via the HTTP protocol are expressed via HTTP error codes (see below). Endpoints define, which response 
codes are sent, when errors occur that are expressable as HTTP status code.</p>

